default3) What are the main challenges associated with providing better and more consistent bus and rail serv
defaultices to isolated communities? How can these challenges be overcome?
default&#xa0;
defaultP
defaultroviding services in sparsely populated areas is expensive and government does not necessarily recognise this in its funding settlements to non-metro transport authorities; cross county 
defaultboundary services can also be a source of problems as different counties can have different priorities in terms of providing 'optional' services; because of vastly varying traffic flows, different types of solutions are necessary for different routes/commu
defaultnities; there should however be core rail and stage carriage routes giving a full regular interval service 
defaultseven days a week.
