default6) What are the main challenges associated
default with funding transport services in isolated communities? How can these services be made more affordable?
default&#xa0;
defaultC
defaultommunity r
defaultail partnerships and community 
defaultbus services have proved their worth in reducing the costs of rural transport even where their activities h
defaultave been largely directed towards increasing revenue - marketing and community involvement strategies have paid dividends in tapping into the suppressed demand mentioned above; the value of improved rural services feeding into national trunk/cross country 
defaultservices needs also to be recognised; for rail, Network Rail have been examining ways of providing cheaper alternative traction options for rural lines. 
